{{ 's-p-about.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'a-about.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

<div class="p">
  <div class="ban">
    <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="{{'im-ban.png' | asset_url}}" media="(min-width: 770px)">
        <img src="{{ 'im-ban-m.png' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </picture>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <section class="s-ab0">
    <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="{{'im-ab0.png' | asset_url}}" media="(min-width: 770px)">
        <img src="{{ 'im-ab0-m.png' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </picture>
    </figure>

    <div>
      <h2>RUGA WAS BUILT ON A SIMPLE IDEA</h2>

      <p>
        Outdoor products should never be the weakest part of the adventure. They should show up, hold their ground, and
        keep going long after the easy options give up. Whatever we create whether it’s something that keeps things
        cold, carries essentials, or supports time spent outdoors it has to earn its place outside, not just look good
        in a photo.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="s-ab1">
    <ul>
      <li>
        <img src="{{ 'im-ls1.webp' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </li>
      <li>
        <img src="{{ 'im-ls2.png' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </li>
      <li>
        <img src="{{ 'im-ls3.webp' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </li>
      <li>
        <img src="{{ 'im-ls4.webp' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      We design for real use. Long days. Rough surfaces. Heat, water, impact, repetition. The kind of environments that
      don’t respond to marketing claims, only to performance. Every Ruga product begins with function and is refined
      with intention. Because serious gear can still be thoughtful. It can be engineered properly and designed with care
      at the same time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="s-ab2">
    <h2>The name Ruga comes from tartaruga the Italian word for <span>TURTLE</span>.</h2>
    <p>
      A creature built with purpose. Protective. Enduring. Designed by nature to move steadily through demanding
      terrain. That mindset shapes everything we do. Strength without noise. Durability without drama. Built to last not
      to impress for a moment.
    </p>
    <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="{{'im-ab2.png' | asset_url}}" media="(min-width: 770px)">
        <img src="{{ 'im-ab2-m.png' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
      </picture>
    </figure>

    <div>
      <h2>RUGA ISN'T ABOUT A SINGLE CATEGORY</h2>
      <p>
        It’s about building a standard across outdoor recreational products pieces that feel solid in your hands,
        dependable in unpredictable conditions, and natural in the environments they’re made for.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="s-ab3">
    <h2>We don’t believe in decorative equipment. We believe in gear that belongs outside.</h2>
    <figure>
      <img src="{{ 'im-ab3.png' | asset_url  }}" width="auto" height="auto" alt="logo">
    </figure>
  </section>
</div>

